    "source": "### 2. Prepare Dataset\n\nCreate your data in JSONL format (one JSON object per line). For SFT with LoRA, the platform expects **prompt/completion** pairs.\n\n**Dataset structure:**\n- Training files under `training/` (or root with `training.jsonl`)\n- Validation files under `validation/` (or `validation.jsonl`)\n\n**SFT format:** Each line is a JSON object with:\n- **`prompt`**: The input (e.g. context + question)\n- **`completion`**: The desired model output",
    "source_html": "<h3>2. Prepare Dataset</h3>\n<p>Create your data in JSONL format (one JSON object per line). For SFT with LoRA, the platform expects <strong>prompt/completion</strong> pairs.</p>\n<p><strong>Dataset structure:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Training files under <code>training/</code> (or root with <code>training.jsonl</code>)</li>\n<li>Validation files under <code>validation/</code> (or <code>validation.jsonl</code>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>SFT format:</strong> Each line is a JSON object with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><code>prompt</code></strong>: The input (e.g. context + question)</li>\n<li><strong><code>completion</code></strong>: The desired model output</li>\n</ul>\n"
